        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 2:25PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 225 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Magic Reservoir, or 12 miles southwest of Hailey,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Magic Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
